## 1. Grant of License

### 1.1 Free Use

You are granted a **worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive license** to:

- **Use** the software for any purpose (personal, educational, research, or commercial)
- **Copy** and distribute the software
- **Modify** the software and create derivative works
- **Distribute** modified versions under the same license terms

### 1.2 Commercial Use - Voluntary Contribution Model

**Commercial use** means using this software in any business, organization, or for-profit activity including:
- Developing paid products or services
- Internal business operations generating revenue
- Consulting services using this software
- SaaS platforms built with this software

**Voluntary Licensing:**
- Commercial users are **encouraged** (but not required) to support the project
- **Suggested contribution:** $5 USD minimum (pay-what-you-want)
- **Honor system:** We trust you to support what you value
- **100% optional:** No technical enforcement, legal obligations, or audits

**How to contribute:**
- GitHub Sponsors: [`https://github.com/sponsors/iberi22`](https://github.com/sponsors/iberi22)
- Open Collective: [`https://opencollective.com/cde-orchestrator`](https://opencollective.com/cde-orchestrator)

